Analysis of Clinical Data for Cushing Patients

This file was last compiled on Tue Feb 24 11:53:34 2015. Unless otherwise noted this analysis removes subject 29.

Statistics

## Warning: attributes are not identical across measure variables; they will
## be dropped

This analysis included 11 controls and 8 cushing patients.

First we checked whether the data was normally distributed using a Shapiro-Wilk test. If a Shapiro-Wilk Normality test had a p-value <0.05 for a measurement in either the control or the cushing cases, we did a Wilcoxon test. This was appropriate for Cer.C14, Cer.C20, Cer.C22..area., Cer.C24, insulin, HOMA.IR, Creatinine, ALT.

We next tested, for the normally distributed data, whether the data had unequal variance. This was done using Levenes test in the car package . A Welchs t-test for unequal variance was appropriate for glucose based on p<0.05. In all other cases, a t-test, presuming equal variance was used.

Correlation with BMI

The HOMA score significantly correlated with the natural logarithm of the BMI (p=0.0051989, r=0.6447761, R2=0.4157362)To correct for the BMI effect on the HOMA-IR score, I generated a linear model comparing the HOMA score to the BMI and the diagnosis. We tested for an interaction between HOMA-IR and BMI in this model, and did not observe any evidence of an interaction (p=0.8697793).

Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)

BMI 1.01 1.10
diagnosisCushings 0.81 2.78

The results of this linear model are a significant main effect of BMI (p=0.0113815) but not the the diagnosis (p=0.1761557) with a r-squared value of 0.4168205. This corresponds to an effect size of 1.5042416.

Model Plot

pdf('../figures/Cushing - BMI-HOMA Correlation.pdf')
with(cushing.data, plot(BMI, log(HOMA.IR),
                           pch=19,las=1,
    col=diagnosis, ylab='Log HOMA-IR Score', xlab="BMI (mg/kg2)"))
legend("topleft", levels(cushing.data$diagnosis)[c(1,3)], pch=19, bty="n", col=palette()[c(1,3)], lty=1)
with(cushing.data[cushing.data$diagnosis == "Control"&cushing.data$id!='29',], abline(lm(log(HOMA.IR)~BMI), col=palette()[1]))
with(cushing.data[cushing.data$diagnosis == "Cushing's"&cushing.data$id!='29',], abline(lm(log(HOMA.IR)~BMI), col=palette()[3]))
dev.off()
